<p>I have put jquery modal in my code.</p>  <pre><code> &lt;script type="text/javascript"&gt;     $(function () {     $('.showDetails').click(function () {         var id = this.id         $("#popup").dialog({             title: "Details",             width: 430,             height: 250,             modal: true,             buttons: {                 Close: function () {                     $(this).dialog('close');                 }             }         });         return false;     }); }) </code></pre>  <p></p>  <p>This modal shows the whenever the user clicks the Details button, it will show the corresponding date using the ID.</p>  <p>In my view:</p>  <p>This is a portion of my table:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;td&gt;               &lt;u&gt;&lt;a href="" id="@rfp.rf_id"  class="showDetails"&gt;Details&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;                                &lt;div id="popup" style="display:none;"&gt;                    @Html.Action("Details",  new { rf_id = rfp.rf_id })                 &lt;/div&gt;           &lt;/td&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Inside the modal, it loads the Details.</p>  <p>In my controller:</p>  <pre><code>public ActionResult Details(int rf_id = 0)     {         var check = db.rms_approval_route_vw.Where(s =&gt; s.rf_id == rf_id).FirstOrDefault();          if (check != null)         {             return PartialView(check);         }         else {             ViewBag.message = "Waiting for regularization.";         }          return PartialView();     } </code></pre>  <p>When I tried to run the code, I clicked the details button, it shows the right information, but when I tried to click the second one, it's the same, and I tried again, it shows the information about the second one. It seems that the data was not updated automatically.</p>  <p>I am using IE11 in running my web.</p>  <p>Thanks a lot for you help.</p>